# Project Meta

- Unity 6.0.3f1, URP, NGO, New Input System; C# 12; async via `Awaitable`.
- UI: UI Toolkit first; data binding preferred where practical.
- Data-driven first: config assets / ScriptableObjects over hardcoded gameplay values.
- `<ProjectName>.Documents/` (GDD/NDD) = design source of truth.

## Organization
- Assets split: `Systems/` (reusable), `Features/` (project), `Core/` (shared glue).
- Per-system `.asmdef` to enforce boundaries.
- `--- SECTION ---` hierarchy separators in scenes.

## Code Commenting
- New/updated editor tooling: concise XML `<summary>` on non-trivial helpers; brief intent comments for non-obvious constants/mappings (for example color palettes).

## Color Literal Formatting
- Custom colors in C# (esp. editor tooling): `new Color32(0xRR, 0xGG, 0xBB, 0xAA)` + nearby `#RRGGBB`/`#RRGGBBAA` comment.
- Named engine constants (for example `Color.white`) fine as-is.
